cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PurpleMCP in academic or applied research, please cite it."
title: "PurpleMCP: A Purple-Team Lab and Benchmark for Model Context Protocol Security"
abstract: >-
  PurpleMCP is a reproducible lab for building, attacking, and defending Model
  Context Protocol (MCP) servers. It pairs 21 intentionally-vulnerable servers
  and working exploits with hardened twins built on a reusable guardrails
  library, maps every module to OWASP LLM Top 10 / CWE / MITRE ATLAS, and ships
  PurpleMCP-Bench — a deterministic guardrail-effectiveness benchmark plus an
  optional LLM-susceptibility evaluation — with machine-readable (JSON/SARIF)
  output and a desktop GUI.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Parshad
    given-names: Kailash
repository-code: "https://github.com/at0m-b0mb/PurpleMCP"
url: "https://github.com/at0m-b0mb/PurpleMCP"
license: MIT
